## P-002: TDD Gate (Harness-Ready Precondition)

| Field      | Value                                                        |
|------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Policy ID  | P-002                                                        |
| Applies To | `build-orchestrator` (consumer), `harness-architect` (producer) |
| Gate Point | Queue building (Step 2) and task claiming (Step 3)           |

**Statement**: The build-orchestrator may only claim and implement a task after the harness-architect has confirmed that the test harness compiles and all tests fail in the red phase.

**Precondition** (build-orchestrator): The task carries the `harness-ready` label.

**Postcondition** (harness-architect): The task has `harness-ready` label, the harness compiles (`{{BUILD_CHECK_COMMAND}}`), and all tests fail with expected failure markers.

**Enforcement** (build-orchestrator): Filter ready queue to only tasks carrying the `harness-ready` label.

**Violation Action**: Halt and suggest running the harness-architect.

